<subSubSection id="C3246572FF94C93BFF62FAC5FDC5FA4E" pageId="53" pageNumber="54" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8B8136F9FF94C93BFF62FAC5FDC5FA4E" blockId="53.[151,1436,1286,1889]" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">
<emphasis id="B94AEAEBFF94C93BFF62FAC5FEC0FAAA" bold="true" box="[199,334,1359,1385]" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific name refers to the native indigenous group that inhabit the 
<typeStatus id="5485885BFF94C93BFB3BFAC5FB40FAAA" box="[1182,1230,1359,1385]" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">type</typeStatus>
locality in Juruti, southwestern 
<collectingRegion id="49FAF81BFF94C93BFE97FAF9FEE9FA4E" box="[306,359,1395,1421]" country="Suriname" name="Para" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">Pará</collectingRegion>
; noun in apposition.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3246572FF94C93BFF62FA1CFAEAF9DE" pageId="53" pageNumber="54" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8B8136F9FF94C93BFF62FA1CFAEAF9DE" blockId="53.[151,1436,1286,1889]" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">
<emphasis id="B94AEAEBFF94C93BFF62FA1CFECCFA73" bold="true" box="[199,322,1430,1456]" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Females of 
<taxonomicName id="4C3E4D7AFF94C93BFE6EFA1DFDFFFA72" authority="Rheims &amp; Jäger, 2022" authorityName="Rheims &amp; Jäger" authorityYear="2022" box="[459,625,1431,1457]" class="Arachnida" family="Sparassidae" genus="Meri" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="53" pageNumber="54" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="munduruku" status="spec. nov.">
<emphasis id="B94AEAEBFF94C93BFE6EFA1DFDFFFA72" box="[459,625,1431,1457]" italics="true" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">M. munduruku</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B94AEAEBFF94C93BFDDDFA1DFD64FA72" bold="true" box="[632,746,1431,1457]" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A2795790FF94C93BFDDDFA1DFD64FA72" box="[632,746,1431,1457]" pageId="53" pageNumber="54" rank="species">spec. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
resemble those 
<taxonomicName id="4C3E4D7AFF94C93BFC05FA1DFBACFA73" authority="Rheims &amp; Jäger, 2022" authorityName="Rheims &amp; Jäger" authorityYear="2022" box="[928,1058,1431,1456]" class="Arachnida" family="Sparassidae" genus="Meri" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="53" pageNumber="54" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="arraijan" status="spec. nov.">
<emphasis id="B94AEAEBFF94C93BFC05FA1DFBACFA73" box="[928,1058,1431,1456]" italics="true" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">M. arraijan</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B94AEAEBFF94C93BFB8FFA1DFB12FA72" bold="true" box="[1066,1180,1431,1457]" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A2795790FF94C93BFB8FFA1DFB12FA72" box="[1066,1180,1431,1457]" pageId="53" pageNumber="54" rank="species">spec. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="13052A7CFF94C93BFB0EFA1DFAC9FA72" box="[1195,1351,1431,1457]" captionStart="FIGURES 118–123" captionStartId="36.[151,264,1318,1342]" captionTargetBox="[156,1421,429,1284]" captionTargetId="figure-95@36.[155,1433,417,1294]" captionTargetPageId="36" captionText="FIGURES 118–123. 118–120 Meri aparia spec. nov., female (ex MNHN 2028, holotype) (118 epigyne, 119 vulva, 120 schematic course of internal duct system); 121–123 Meri arraijan spec. nov., female (AMNH, paratype) (121 epigyne, 122 vulva, 123 schematic course of internal duct system). ag—anterior groove; EP—epigynal pocket; ft—first turn of duct system; FD— fertilization duct; GP—glandular projection; LL—lateral lobe; MS—median septum; SP—spermathecae. Scale lines: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6550283" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6550283/files/figure.png" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">Figs 121–123</figureCitation>
) by the irregular hexagon shape of the MS, wider than long and widest anteriorly, in the epigyne. They are distinguished from the latter species by the pair of anterior grooves in the epigynal field (
<figureCitation id="13052A7CFF94C93BFC47FA55FBCEFA3A" box="[994,1088,1503,1529]" captionStart="FIGURES 208–216" captionStartId="54.[151,264,1743,1767]" captionTargetBox="[155,1418,195,1708]" captionTargetId="figure-23@54.[155,1432,181,1720]" captionTargetPageId="54" captionText="FIGURES 208–216. 208–210 Meri mathani (Simon) comb. nov., female (MNHN 2028, lectotype) (208 epigyne, 209 vulva, 210 schematic course of internal duct system); 211–213 Meri munduruku spec. nov., female (MPEG 30776, holotype) (211 epigyne, 212 vulva 213 schematic course of internal duct system); 214–216 Meri paiaia spec. nov., female (IBSP 167988, holotype) (214 epigyne, 215 vulva, 216 schematic course of internal duct system). EP—epigynal pocket; FD—fertilization duct; ft—first turn of duct system; GP—glandular projection; LL—lateral lobe; MS—median septum; SP—spermathecae. Scale lines: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6550344" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6550344/files/figure.png" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">Fig. 211</figureCitation>
) and by the internal ducts with FW dilated (
<figureCitation id="13052A7CFF94C93BFE86F989FE0AF9DE" box="[291,388,1539,1565]" captionStart="FIGURES 208–216" captionStartId="54.[151,264,1743,1767]" captionTargetBox="[155,1418,195,1708]" captionTargetId="figure-23@54.[155,1432,181,1720]" captionTargetPageId="54" captionText="FIGURES 208–216. 208–210 Meri mathani (Simon) comb. nov., female (MNHN 2028, lectotype) (208 epigyne, 209 vulva, 210 schematic course of internal duct system); 211–213 Meri munduruku spec. nov., female (MPEG 30776, holotype) (211 epigyne, 212 vulva 213 schematic course of internal duct system); 214–216 Meri paiaia spec. nov., female (IBSP 167988, holotype) (214 epigyne, 215 vulva, 216 schematic course of internal duct system). EP—epigynal pocket; FD—fertilization duct; ft—first turn of duct system; GP—glandular projection; LL—lateral lobe; MS—median septum; SP—spermathecae. Scale lines: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6550344" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6550344/files/figure.png" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">Fig. 212</figureCitation>
) (anterior groove single and FW slender in 
<taxonomicName id="4C3E4D7AFF94C93BFCC9F989FC61F9DF" authority="Rheims &amp; Jäger, 2022" authorityName="Rheims &amp; Jäger" authorityYear="2022" box="[876,1007,1539,1564]" class="Arachnida" family="Sparassidae" genus="Meri" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="53" pageNumber="54" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="arraijan" status="spec. nov.">
<emphasis id="B94AEAEBFF94C93BFCC9F989FC61F9DF" box="[876,1007,1539,1564]" italics="true" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">M. arraijan</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B94AEAEBFF94C93BFC53F989FBE7F9DE" bold="true" box="[1014,1129,1539,1565]" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A2795790FF94C93BFC53F989FBE7F9DE" box="[1014,1129,1539,1565]" pageId="53" pageNumber="54" rank="species">spec. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
). Males are unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3246572FF94C93BFF62F9ACFE0AF8FE" pageId="53" pageNumber="54" type="description">
<paragraph id="8B8136F9FF94C93BFF62F9ACFDADF8DA" blockId="53.[151,1436,1286,1889]" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">
<emphasis id="B94AEAEBFF94C93BFF62F9ACFDCBF983" bold="true" box="[199,581,1574,1601]" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">
Description. Female (
<typeStatus id="5485885BFF94C93BFE6FF9ACFDB6F983" box="[458,568,1574,1600]" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">holotype</typeStatus>
):
</emphasis>
